HEADWORD: Defecation
<hw>Def`e*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>defaecatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧f⟦eacute⟧cation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
separating from impurities, as lees or dregs; purification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The act or process of voiding
excrement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defecator</ent>⟦br⟧
